<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ890907-0024 </DOCNO><DD> = 890907 </DD><AN> 890907-0024. </AN><HL> EGandamp;G Division Wins@  $212 Million Contract@  For Army Facility </HL><DD> 09/07/89 </DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J) </SO><CO> EGG GE FMC WX GM GMH BP ALD HON RTN </CO><IN> AEROSPACE (ARO) </IN><GV> DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </GV><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   EGandamp;G Inc.'s defense materials division won a $212 million Army contract for construction of a chemical weapons-destruction facility.    General Electric Co. was given $147.9 million in Army contracts for armored-vehicle transmissions and support of the air defense anti-tank system.    FMC Corp. received a $78.2 million Army contract for armored personnel carriers.    Westinghouse Electric Corp. got $76.7 million in contracts for Navy Trident missile launchers and radar-antenna research for the Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency.    Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp., was awarded $56.8 million in Army contracts for M-1 tank sights and range finders.    The Sohio division of British Petroleum Co. received an $18.6 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for jet fuel.    Allied-Signal Aerospace Co., a unit of Allied-Signal Inc., won a $16 million Navy contract for shipboard weapons systems.    Honeywell Inc. was given a $14.6 million Army contract for communications equipment.    Raytheon Co. received an $11.6 million Army contract for Patriot missile support. </TEXT></DOC>